summary: “here’s to a thousand years of you.” … “besides. you know i’m in love with you, right?” a vax/keyleth playlist. tracklist below...
caption:
“here’s to a thousand years of you.” … “besides. you know i’m in love with you, right?”

a vax/keyleth playlist.

tracklist below the cut.

she’s got you high // mumm-ra

the sun’s in the sky, it makes for happy endings / you can’t deny you want the happy ending

earth // imogen heap

the cold shoulder, folded arms, the looking up / you’ve never listened, carry on careless, regardless

tattooed tears // the front bottoms

but if you listen to your heart it may mislead you / lord, i should know, i’ve felt lost for so long

please don’t say you love me // gabrielle aplin

how we feel is hard to fake / so let’s not give the game away

i bet my life // imagine dragons

i know i took the path that you would never want for me / i know i let you down, didn’t i

hey, hey, hey // delta rae

i tried to love you babe and i’m trying still / i’ve always loved you babe and i always will

breakable // ingrid michaelson

so it’s fairly simple to cut right through the mess / and the to stop the muscle that makes us confess

fools // lauren aquilina

i want you more than i’ve wanted anyone / isn’t that dangerous?

jesus christ // brand new

well jesus christ i’m not scared to die / i’m a little bit scared of what comes after

holding a heart // toby lightman

i’ll try all i can to find a soft place to land / calm down, calm down, calm down

the ballad of love and hate // the avett brothers

he says, “love i’m sorry” and she says “what for? / i’m yours and that’s it, whatever.”

after the storm // mumford & sons

get over your hill and see what you find there / with grace in your heart and flowers in your hair

overture (instrumental) // sleeping at last

instrumental

heroes // mika

i wish there was a way to give you a hand to hold / you don’t have to die in your glory / die to never grow old

wanderer’s lullaby // adriana figueroa

you have walked this path since your birth / you were destined for more

somewhere only we know // lily allen

is this the place we used to love? / is this the place that i’ve been dreaming of?

in the wind // lord huron

take your time, let the rivers guide you in / you know where you can find me again / i’ll be waiting here til the stars fall out of the sky

signs // bloc party

i believe in anything / that brings you back home to me

light // sleeping at last

you are loved, you are loved more than you know / i hereby pledge all of my days to prove it so

landslide // the dixie chicks

well, i’ve been afraid of changing cause i built my life around you / but time makes you bolder, even children get older / and i’m getting older, too

blackbird // evan rachel wood

all your life, you were only waiting for this moment to be free
